The paper uses deep generative models (GANs) to represent the distribution of rock properties and perform history matching for a hydrocarbon reservoir model. This involves solving an ill-posed inverse problem using gradient descent on the latent variables of the GAN. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with machine learning and optimization. The paper also uses geostatistical object-based models, which could fall under cs.CV (computer vision) or cs.SI (signal processing). Finally, the paper involves modeling fluid flow and transport, which could be relevant to cs.NE (neural networks) as well.
